{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01X1h1wm26dqYTcHESDoWXcc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WfhuFXxcn6BkVvmuRYHpuE","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/short/r7/spark-day2-operations-adversary-20260703_080813/stages/stage_03/submit.txt","content":"ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS\n===================\n\nStage 3 (aggregate by user_id) fails with an OutOfMemoryError because:\n\n1. MEMORY MISCONFIGURATION: The ETL job was configured with only 256m of\n   driver/executor memory. In local[2] mode, the executor runs inside the\n   driver JVM. A 256m heap is below Spark's minimum reserved system memory\n   (~471MB), so spark-submit fails immediately with:\n   \"must be at least ... increase heap size\"\n\n2. DATA SKEW (compounding factor): user_id 999 holds ~50% of all records,\n   causing a single reduce task in Stage 3 to receive a disproportionate\n   data load, exhausting available heap even if memory were marginally\n   sufficient.\n\n   Data distribution:\n   - total_records:       100,000\n   - distinct_user_ids:   1,000\n   - hot_user_id:         999\n   - hot_user_records:    50,000  (50% of total)\n   - skew_ratio:          500x    (threshold: 10x)\n\nDIAGNOSIS SOURCE\n================\n- kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=diagnostic-server:\n    DIAGNOSTIC: hot key user_id=999 holds ~50% of records\n    DIAGNOSTIC: skew_ratio=500x (>> 10x threshold)\n    DIAGNOSTIC: Stage 3 GROUP BY user_id triggers OutOfMemoryError\n- /data/skew_info.txt (data-generator pod): confirmed above figures\n\nFIX APPLIED\n===========\nRaised driver and executor memory from 256m -> 1g in\ncases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml:\n\n  --driver-memory 1g\n  --conf spark.executor.memory=1g\n\nAlso enabled AQE skew-join handling to mitigate the data-skew factor:\n\n  --conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true\n  --conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true\n\nRe-applied the job:\n  kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n  kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n\nVERIFICATION\n============\n- kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl  ->  STATUS: Complete  (1/1)\n- Job logs contain: \"spark_etl_pipeline_verified\"\n- All three pipeline stages (load, clean/transform, aggregate) completed\n  without OOM errors under the new 1g memory allocation\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":792,"cache_read_input_tokens":50984,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":792},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f55a0797-00e9-4729-b96a-6515335e4e2d","uuid":"1e923430-14e1-4182-905c-14c80b467c28","request_id":"req_011CceoKi5VzBYxFu3zwktdf"}
